secondaryRef.secondary: protein maturation by copper ion transfer
protein maturation by copper ion transfer

attributeList.attribute: Copper chaperone for superoxide dismutase which delivers copper to the [Cu-Zn] superoxide dismutase I (SOD1, CPX-2896) forming heterodimer (CPX-2267). Insertion of copper is required for SOD1 enzymatic activity. Oxidation of an intramolecular disulfide bond is required to increase the enzymatic activity from approximately 10 % in disulfide-reduced SOD1 to 100 % in disulfide-oxidized SOD1. The copper chaperone, CCS1, both delivers the copper and oxidises the disulfide bond.
